Director Cell Culture Technology Center, Cell Therapy - Mod Cell Culture


Bayer’s cell culture team supports the development of emerging therapies in Bayer's portfolio with an emphasis on oncology, cardiology and additional specialty care therapeutic areas. We work closely with a network of health care professionals, patients, academic centers, other pharmaceutical companies, and innovative biotech organizations to bring innovative treatments to market. By combining automation, digital capabilities and single-use bioprocessing technologies, we streamline production to bring new medicines to patients faster.

This role will provide strategic leadership for Production activities for Cell Therapy (CT-Mod) Production. Manages manufacturing operations for the cell therapy area and all other production operations tasks and responsibilities. Responsible for production safety and regulatory compliance. Assures continuous compliance and process improvements of production operations and technology transfers / New Product Introductions. Shared responsibilities with QA for department quality management, Quality systems implementation, and Process Validation, and shared responsibilities with Engineering / Maintenance for equipment / facility works.

YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Director Cell Culture Technology Center, Cell Therapy - Mod Cell Culture, are to:
Lead staffing of plant production team for cell therapy manufacturing;
Build high performing team and a team culture that is strictly aligned with LIFE values;
Ensure timely onboarding of personnel to maximize training opportunities and to deliver all process and / or facility validation requirements;
Work with site teams to integrate with and influence established site systems as needed to implement new cell therapy production operations;
Create visibility on site integration activities and/or gaps and establish processes for site integration with CT-Mod (or vice versa);
Develop all cell therapy/ cell culture production procedures and integrate new operation in Berkeley site;
Serve as the primary operations technical expert;
Have knowledge in cell therapy production, mammalian cell culture and GMP aseptic manufacturing processes;
Carrie operational accountability to drive development of Current Good Manufacturing Practices (cGMP) process qualification and validation strategies that ensure agile project implementation, production activities and tech transfers;
Lead qualification of processes and / or facility as needed for Production and to ensure readiness for product introduction;
Develop manufacturing area plan and systems/processes that support both the project and operationalizing the CT-Mod facility;
Manage manufacturing activities for cell therapy, including cGMP aseptic processes, expansion and differentiation of pluripotent stem cells and formulation of cell therapeutics;
Coordinate the production operation with focus on plant turnaround, product introduction and launch, product/viral segregation, throughput scheduling needs and equipment monitoring;
Adhere to clinical and launch supply chain targets by meeting or exceeding monthly and annual production output demand;
Establish, track and meet metrics for area;
Ensure adherence to release process and cycle time targets;
Continuously seek process improvement opportunities and take action accordingly;
Work cross functionally to develop an efficient and compliant process for area change over and, if needed, multi-product manufacturing in a single use facility;
Demonstrate commitment to safety by driving a safety culture and engaging in all safety initiatives;
Be responsible for department cost center by reviewing monthly costs;
Look for opportunities to reduce costs and to operate more efficiently;
Prepare and adhere to production output and operating budgets for department;
Exert proper control and managing of expenses and use of resources, scraps, invoices etc.;
Ensure Production areas and processes are maintained in excellent cGMP conditions at all times;
Ensure that all compliance commitments are met;
Ensure the plant, processes and personnel are inspection ready at all times and prepare the plant for inspection by external authorities and internal audits;
Drive Quality mindset through ownership and self-assessments;
Continuously seek opportunities for improving overall compliance and discrepancies;
Track deviation generation and ensure that adverse trends are addressed quickly and effectively;
Provide direction and / or act as escalation point for unresolved deviations / non conformances;
Partner with Quality unit and Engineering representatives to implement effective corrective and preventative actions (CAPAs) to prevent reoccurrence;
Participate in the technical process review and approve all new or modified products to be manufactured within CT Mod (Cell Therapy), before submitting for Regulatory Agency approval and / or release for clinical / commercial (launch) manufacturing;
Provide effective leadership including developing and implementing objectives and business strategies, building a capable and lean CT Mod Production team, challenging employees to develop as leaders while serving as a role model and mentor, performing Performance calibration/Talend Pool Management/Succession Planning, individual goal setting and performance reviews, training and development, supporting workforce diversity, supporting area managers/associate directors in management of their teams/departments;
Manage employee performance issues and corrective actions;
Mitigate conflict and communication problems;
Recognize and appreciate employee contributions;
Plan and facilitate team activities;
Lead all manufacturing aspects of Tech Transfer including, but not limited to assessment of new product requirements against processes, generation of product specific documentation, supporting the introduction of new equipment, raw materials and / or consumables, determine safety implications if any and training of personnel;
Develop processes for efficient introduction of new products to CCTC;
Develop metrics to track efficiency.

WHO YOU ARE

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor of Science and at least 10 years of experience or Master of Science and at least eight years of experience or Ph.D. and at least six years of experience, manufacturing experience in pharmaceutical operations, or an equivalent combination of education and experience;
At least five years as people manager;
Broad and deep understanding of biotech manufacturing requirements in the pharmaceutical industry;
Ability to monitor and control processes using data trending and / or statistical process control;
Proven ability to trouble shoot issues and resolve issues;
Thorough knowledge and application of Good Manufacturing Practices;
Understanding of cGMP Directives, industry guidelines and applicable agency regulation (FDA, EMA, etc.) particularly as they relate to cell and gene therapy;
Solid knowledge of viral segregation requirements;
Strong leadership skills, ability to communicate and partner well with all levels of staff, to lead and motivate with emphasis on compliance and continuous improvement and to resolve conflicts;
Provide vision and strategy for Area that are in-line with business goals and objectives;
