Provide direction to direct reports towards achieving department goals and objectives, and engages in strategic discussions with leaders from across the business;
Empowers others, can c reate a strong team morale and reward team efforts;
Foster open and transparent communication within the team and department;
Put a high priority on developing others through coaching, feedback, exposure and stretch assignments;
Treat colleagues from all levels as internal customers;
Interact and respond to requests respectively;
Gain insight into customer needs;
Represent own interests while being fair to others and their areas;
Partner to get work done.

Preferred Qualifications:

Experience in pharmaceutical operations in biotech;
Cell Therapy Experience;
Highly familiar with all of the following manufacturing areas, aseptic processes, expansion and differentiation of pluripotent stem cells (allogenic and/or autologous) in adherent and suspension cultures, formulation of cell therapeutics, media and solution preparation and weigh/dispense.

